UNIVERSITY OF NORTH CAROLINA HERBARIUM
NCU00135778

Flora of the Southeastern United States of America

State: North Carolina
Family: DIAPENSIACEAE
County: Surry

Taxon: *Galax urceolata*

Location: Big Pinnacle Trail at Pilot Mountain State Park, ¼ mile E of Summit Parking Lot, found immediately after the beginning of the trail on North side of the ridge.

Habitat: Shaded and semi-mesic habitat with prominent *Rhododendron* and *Kalmia* species and some mosses (chestnut oak-heath community). Sparse canopy of *Q. montana*.

Comments: Found in small groupings in shaded areas, generally in groups of 10-30 individuals. Often present under Rhododendrons.

Collector: Spencer Scheidt (Handwritten)
Date Collected: 2010 October 8 (Handwritten)

University of North Carolina Herbarium (NCU)
Chapel Hill, North Carolina, United States of America
